						               													<description>This is an economic game self-published bye Joe Zihlmann from Switzerland.&amp;#10;Winner of the game is the player who first build a trust of 7 companies. The 5 different kind of companies must be part of the winning trust.&amp;#10;Every player starts with 2 companies, fixed by the rules.&amp;#10;The 5 different companies are:&amp;#10;Producer of oil, Producer of metal, Producer of energy, a Factory and a commerce.&amp;#10;Every player has industry-terrain on which he places his company and the elements produced there.&amp;#10;The producers supply the resources, and the factory  builds the end-product with 1 of the three resources.  Then with the commerce you try to sell that product to the market.&amp;#10;In addition, all things can be traded between the players or the market (when available).&amp;#10;The Market is defined with a &amp;quot;wheel&amp;quot;, in every round it will be turned/shuffled and shows the buy- and sell-numbers for this turn.&amp;#10;A Turn (all players):&amp;#10;1. Shuffle the market&amp;#10;2. Player produce resources.&amp;#10;3. Buy and/or trade resources with the market and/or the  other players.&amp;#10;4. Production of end-products from the players factories&amp;#10;5. All players try to sell their end-products&amp;#10;6. All players must pay their storage-costs and taxes&amp;#10;7. Buy or sell of companies.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
